Welcome to the Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy explains what personal data the UnionToken Application collects and what we do with it. Please take the time to read through it carefully. If you have any questions, please send us an email at customerservice@unionbankng.com.
Summary
Using the following services, we collect your data for the following purposes:
• Access to Third-party accounts: Facebook account access
Permissions: Access Friend Lists and activities
• Analytics: Google analytics with anonymised IP
Data collected: Cookies and usage data
• Device permissions for access to personal data
Data collected: Approximate location permission (continuous), camera permission and contacts permission
• Location-based interactions: Geolocation
Data collected: Geographic position
‍
Privacy Policy
‍
Data Controller and Owner
Types of Data collected
This Application collects personal data by itself or through third parties. Such data includes geographic position, cookies, usage data, contacts permission, camera permission and approximate location permission (continuous).
Other personal data collected may be described in other sections of this Privacy Policy or by dedicated explanation text contextually with the data collection.
The User's personal data may be freely provided or collected automatically when using this Application.
The use of cookies – or other tracking tools – by this Application or by the owners of third-party services used by this Application, unless stated otherwise, serves to identify Users and
remember their preferences for the sole purpose of providing personalised services to our customers.
When we are unable to collect personal data, it makes it impossible for us to provide the services of this Application.
Ultimately, you are responsible for any personal data of third parties obtained, published or shared through this Application and must confirm that you have the third party's consent to provide the data
‍
Mode and place of processing Data
Methods of Processing
The Data Controller processes your data in a proper manner and will take appropriate security measures to prevent unauthorised access, disclosure, modification, or unauthorised destruction of the data. We process data using computers and/or IT enabled tools, following organisational procedures and modes strictly related to the purposes indicated. In some cases, the data may be accessible to persons appointed as Data Processors by the owner. Such persons are usually involved with the operation of the site, e.g., administration, sales, marketing, legal, system administration or external parties (such as third-party technical service providers, mail carriers, hosting providers, IT companies, communications agencies. The updated list of these parties may be requested from the Data Controller at any time.
Place
The Data is processed at the Data Controller's operating offices and in any other places where the parties involved with the processing are located. For more information, please contact the Data Controller.
‍
Retention time
The Data is kept for the required time as prescribed by the Data Controller Policy to provide the services you request, or as stated by the purposes outlined in this document. You can always request that the Data Controller suspend or remove the data.
‍
The use of the collected Data
We collect your information to provide you with better and personalised services, including location-based interactions, analytics, access to third-party accounts, and device permissions for personal data access.
The personal data used for each purpose is outlined in specific sections of this document.
Facebook permissions requested by this Application
This Application may require some Facebook permissions to allow it to perform actions with your Facebook account and retrieve information, including personal data. This service allows
this Application to connect with the User's account on the Facebook social network, provided by Facebook Inc.
For more information about the following permissions, please refer to the Facebook permissions documentation and to the Facebook Privacy Policy.
The permissions asked are:
• Basic information
By default, this includes specific data such as corporate name, Corporate ID, username, name, picture, gender, and your locale. Certain connections of yours, such as friends, are also available. If you have made more of your data public, more information will be available.
• Access Friend Lists
Provides access to any friend lists you have created
• Activities
Provides access to your list of activities
• Device permissions for personal data access
Depending on your specific device, this Application may request certain permissions that allow it to access your device data as described below.
By default, you are required to grant these permissions before information can be accessed. Once permission has been granted, you can revoke it at any time. To revoke these permissions, please refer to your device settings or contact the owner for support using the contact details provided in this document.
The exact procedure for controlling app permissions may be dependent on your device and software.
Please note that the revoking of such permissions might impact the proper functioning of this Application.
If you grant any of the permissions listed below, the respective personal data may be processed, i.e. accessed,modified or removed by this Application.
• Approximate location permission (continuous)
Used for accessing your approximate device location. This Application may collect, use, and share your location data to provide location-based services.
• Camera permission
Used for accessing the camera or capturing images and video from the device.
• Contacts permission
Used for accessing contacts and profiles on your device, including the changing of entries.
Additional information about Data Collection and Processing
Legal action
Your data may be used for legal purposes by the Data Controller in court or during the stages leading to possible legal action arising from improper use of this Application or its related services.
By using this Application, you declare to be aware that the Data Controller may be required to reveal personal data when needed to the public, judicial or regulatory authorities.
‍
Additional information about your corporate or Personal Data
In addition to the information contained in this Privacy Policy, this Application may provide you with additional and contextual information concerning particular services or the collection and processing of personal data upon request.
System logs and maintenance
For operation and maintenance purposes, this Application and any third-party services may collect files that record interaction with this Application (System logs) or use other personal data such as IP addresses for this purpose.
‍
Information not contained in this Policy
More details concerning the collection or processing of personal data may be requested from the Data Controller at any time. Please see the contact information at the beginning of this document.
Your Rights
You have the right, at any time, to know whether your corporate or personal data has been stored and can consult the Data Controller to learn about their contents and origin, to verify their accuracy or to ask for them to be supplemented, cancelled, updated or corrected, or for their transformation into anonymous format or to block any data held in violation of the law, as well as to oppose their treatment for any and all legitimate reasons. Requests should be sent to the Data Controller at the contact information set out above.
This Application does not support "Do Not Track" requests.
To determine whether any third-party services it uses honour the "Do Not Track" requests, please read their privacy policies
‍
Changes to this Privacy Policy
The Data Controller reserves the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy at any time by giving notice to its Users on this page. We strongly recommend that you check this page often, referring to the date of the last modification listed at the bottom. If you object to any of the changes to the Policy, you must cease using this Application and can request that the Data Controller remove your personal data. Unless stated otherwise, the then-current Privacy Policy applies to all personal data the Data Controller has about you.
Information about this Privacy Policy
The Data Controller is responsible for this Privacy Policy, prepared starting from the modules provided by Union Bank and hosted on Union Bank's servers.
